cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper presents a liver lesion detection model using a Single Shot MultiBox Detector (SSD) and custom-designed multi-phase computed tomography (CT) volumes. The focus is on computer vision and machine learning techniques for object detection, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of grouped convolutions and the training and evaluation of the modified SSD model, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of CT volumes and the detection of liver lesions may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
